task_description: Facing the building to your South-West (approx. 232°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving closer to the target building via the front-left available move will provide a clearer view of its full structure, making it easier to estimate the total height by counting floors or assessing proportions.
Moving front will bring me closer to the area of the target southwest building, making it easier to view and assess its full height once I adjust my facing direction.
Based on the visible multi-story building in front, estimating 8 floors at approximately 3 meters per floor gives a total height of 24 meters.
